<header>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="twelve columns">
      <h1>The Grid</h1>
      <h4>Flexible, efficient layout.</h4>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="mainContent">

  <div class="row">

    <div class="ten columns push-two">
      <p class="show-for-small"><a href="<%= root_path %>">&larr; Back to Home</a></p>
    	<%= image_tag "feature-grid-1.png" %>
      <h4>Flexible, efficient layout.</h4>
      <p>You've probably used a grid framework before &mdash; we think you'll like this one. It's a 12-column flexible grid that can scale out to an arbitrary size (defined by the max-width of the row) that's also easily nested, so you can build out complicated layouts without creating a lot of custom elements. And when the Grid isn't enough for your site, it just gets out of the way. <br/> <a href="<%= docs_grid_path %>">Grid docs &rarr;</a></p>

      <h4>Examples</h4>
      <div class="row">
      	<div class="four columns">
      	  <%= link_to examples_grid_path(id:1), target: "_blank" do %>
      	    <%= image_tag "feature-grid-2.png" %>
      	    <p>All Grid Sizes</p>
      	  <% end %>
      	</div>
      	<div class="four columns">
      	  <%= link_to examples_grid_path(id:2), target: "_blank" do %>
      	    <%= image_tag "feature-grid-3.png" %>
      	    <p>Nesting the Grid</p>
      	  <% end %>
      	</div>
      	<div class="four columns">
      	  <%= link_to examples_grid_path(id:3), target: "_blank" do %>
      	    <%= image_tag "feature-grid-4.png" %>
      	    <p>Mobile Grids</p>
      	  <% end %>
      	</div>
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="two columns pull-ten">
      <%= render "sidebar" %>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>
